#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.55"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.55:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.55:0.2"
msgid "6. Dukkhavagga"
msgstr "6. Suffering"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.55:0.3"
msgid "55. Mahārukkhasutta"
msgstr "55. A Great Tree"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.55:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.55:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Upādāniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā pavaḍḍhati."
msgstr ""
"“There are things that are prone to being grasped. When you concentrate on "
"the gratification provided by these things, your craving grows."

msgctxt "sn12.55:1.3"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ;"
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping."

msgctxt "sn12.55:1.4"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo … pe …"
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. …"

msgctxt "sn12.55:1.5"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.55:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahārukkho."
msgstr "Suppose there was a great tree."

msgctxt "sn12.55:2.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa yāni ceva mūlāni adhogamāni, yāni ca tiriyaṅgamāni, sabbāni tāni "
"uddhaṃ ojaṃ abhiharanti."
msgstr "And its roots going downwards and across all draw the sap upwards."

msgctxt "sn12.55:2.3"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, mahārukkho tadāhāro tadupādāno ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ "
"tiṭṭheyya."
msgstr ""
"Fueled and sustained by that, the great tree would stand for a long time."

msgctxt "sn12.55:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, upādāniyesu dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā "
"pavaḍḍhati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are things that are prone to being grasped. When you "
"concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, your craving "
"grows."

msgctxt "sn12.55:2.5"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. …"

msgctxt "sn12.55:2.6"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.88"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.55:3.1"
msgid ""
"Upādāniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"There are things that are prone to being grasped. When you concentrate on "
"the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.55:3.2"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho;"
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.55:3.3"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. …"

msgctxt "sn12.55:3.4"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.55:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahārukkho."
msgstr "Suppose there was a great tree."

#. VAR: kuddālapiṭakaṃ → kudālapiṭakaṃ (aññattha)
msgctxt "sn12.55:4.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya."
msgstr "Then a person comes along with a spade and basket."

#. VAR: palikhaṇeyya → palikhaneyya (s2, s3) | paliṃ khaṇeyya (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.55:4.3"
msgid ""
"So taṃ rukkhaṃ mūle chindeyya, mūlaṃ chinditvā palikhaṇeyya, palikhaṇitvā "
"mūlāni uddhareyya antamaso usīranāḷimattānipi."
msgstr ""
"They’d cut the tree down at the roots, dig it up, and pull the roots out, "
"down to the fibers and stems."

msgctxt "sn12.55:4.4"
msgid ""
"So taṃ rukkhaṃ khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chindeyya, khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chinditvā "
"phāleyya, phāletvā sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ kareyya, sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ karitvā "
"vātātape visoseyya;"
msgstr ""
"They’d cut the tree apart, cut up the parts, and chop it into splinters. "
"They’d dry the splinters in the wind and sun, burn them with fire, and "
"reduce them to ashes. Then they’d winnow the ashes in a strong wind, or "
"float them away down a swift stream."

#. VAR: ophuṇeyya → opuneyya (bj, pts1-2) | ophuneyya (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.55:4.5"
msgid ""
"vātātape visosetvā agginā ḍaheyya, agginā ḍahetvā masiṃ kareyya, masiṃ "
"karitvā mahāvāte vā ophuṇeyya nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāheyya."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: anabhāvaṃkato → anabhāvakato (bj) | anabhāvaṅgato (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn12.55:4.6"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, mahārukkho ucchinnamūlo assa tālāvatthukato "
"anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""
"In this way the great tree is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, "
"obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "sn12.55:4.7"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, upādāniyesu dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā "
"nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are things that are prone to being grasped. When you "
"concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.55:4.8"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho;"
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.55:4.9"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. …"

msgctxt "sn12.55:4.10"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.55:4.11"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
